message.content:
cs.NI, cs.MA, cs.SY, cs.CR, cs.DC

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper proposes a cooperative system utilizing device-to-device communication architecture underlaying LTE to improve smartphone battery life. This falls under the networking and internet architecture sub-category.
2. cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) - The proposed system involves users with high battery levels helping carry the traffic of users with low battery levels. This can be seen as a multiagent system where agents (users) cooperate to achieve a common goal.
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The proposed system involves controlling the flow of traffic in the network to increase the amount of valued battery. This falls under the systems and control sub-category.
4. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper may touch upon security concerns related to device-to-device communication and the sharing of battery levels between users. This falls under the cryptography and security sub-category.
5. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The proposed system involves distributed computing where users with high battery levels act as relays to carry traffic for users with low battery levels. This falls under the distributed, parallel, and cluster computing sub-category.
